[It is suspected, but not confirmed yet, that the dog was imported
illegally. As the references below indicate, importation of companion
animals into France from North Africa has in the past posed risk of
transmission of rabies.

The Vendee is a department in the Pays-de-la-Loire region in west
central France, on the Atlantic Ocean. The name Vendee is taken from
the Vendee river which runs through the south eastern part of the
department. The HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of France can be
accessed at: http://healthmap.org/r/00Fc. - Mod.CP]
